modules.description: This module defines structures to match API methods and paths for access control. It supports matching exact or wildcard path segments and HTTP methods, with configurations to allow or deny access by default while specifying exceptions. Use cases include restricting access to specific API endpoints based on method and path patterns, such as allowing GET requests on `/users/*` but denying access to `/admin/*`.

This module provides functions to define and evaluate access control rules for API endpoints based on HTTP methods and path patterns. It supports exact matches, wildcards, and default allow or deny policies with configurable exceptions. Use it to restrict access to routes like allowing `GET` on `/users/*` while blocking `/admin/*` in a web application.
